  "prompt": "What does \"followed by None\" mean in Instagram search?",
  "response": "On Instagram, when you see \"followed by None\" in search results, it typically indicates that the account you are viewing is not followed by anyone you are connected to, or that it is a private account and those you follow do not have any mutual followers with that account. This message can appear when looking at accounts, posts, or hashtags, suggesting that there are no connections or mutual friends associated with that particular content. It can also indicate that the account is relatively obscure or less popular among your network.",
